{"type":"message","id":"5f972f20","parentId":"5b88a43d","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:24:32.482Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 14:24 GMT+2] FINAL HFT PREP: HOT RELOAD & TARGETS.\n\n1.  **Hot Reload (Windows-Safe):**\n    *   Edit `src/agent_wrapper.py`.\n    *   Add background thread monitoring `docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` (check `os.path.getmtime`).\n    *   On change: Reload config/instructions in memory. Log \"Hot Reload: Active\".\n\n2.  **DMarket Client Upgrade (`dmarket_api.py`):**\n    *   Implement `create_target(game_id, item_id, price_coins)` using Signature v2.\n    *   Implement `get_last_sales(item_title)` to filter peaks.\n    *   Refactor `get_market_prices` to support `game_id` (CS2, Rust, TF2).\n\n3.  **Steam Background Thread:**\n    *   Modify `trade_logic.py`: Move Steam calls to `asyncio.create_task(update_steam_prices())` loop (run every 10m).\n    *   Main loop `monitor_prices` MUST NOT await Steam.\n\n4.  **Master Protocol Update:**\n    *   Add \"Scalable Models\" section: Pro (Hourly Trend Analysis), Flash (Per-Transaction Validation).\n\n5.  **Final Profit Scan:**\n    *   Scan 5 items (CS2/Rust) with `Target Price` strategy.\n    *   Calculate Net Profit = `(Lowest Ask * 0.93) - Target Bid`.\n\n6.  **Output:**\n    *   Confirmed `agent_wrapper.py` update.\n    *   Confirmed `dmarket_api.py` methods.\n    *   5 Arbitrage Chains.\n    *   Ready Signal."}],"timestamp":1771158272480}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f4f6139","parentId":"5f972f20","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:24:37.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Assessing HFT Requirements**\n\nI've just begun a thorough analysis of the user's HFT request. The initial stages involve decoding the specific code modifications, and protocol adjustments required. I'm focusing on parsing the user's intent to define the key tasks, as well as breaking down the scope of market scanning into measurable steps.\n\n\n**Deciphering the Code**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the code changes. I'll need to focus on implementing a hot reload feature that monitors the protocol document. First, I'll modify the agent wrapper to watch for updates. After that, I will incorporate the protocol file to define the market scan requirements.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771158277317_666","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Depth 2"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158277422_667","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/agent_wrapper.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158277528_668","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"dmarket_api.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158277635_669","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"trade_logic.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158277753_670","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5229,"output":173,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5402,"cost":{"input":0.010458,"output":0.002076,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012534}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771158272482}}
