{"type":"message","id":"3b825e0d","parentId":"dec1864e","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:24:57.719Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting File Locations**\n\nI've successfully located the key files within the specified directory structure. Specifically, I've confirmed the existence and pathing for `agent_wrapper.py`, `dmarket_api.py`, and `trade_logic.py`. Next, I will look at the `docs_archive/MASTER` to begin my analysis.\n\n\n**Planning Further Actions**\n\nI've mapped out the next steps for implementation. Firstly, I'll enhance the hot reload functionality within `src/agent_wrapper.py`. I'll create a thread to monitor `docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` and log a \"Hot Reload: Active\" message upon any changes, as requested. Secondly, I will familiarize myself with `dmarket_api.py` and `trade_logic.py`.\n\n\n**Outlining Implementation Strategy**\n\nI'm now formulating a detailed action plan. Specifically, I'll first address the hot reload feature in `src/agent_wrapper.py`, creating a thread to watch `docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` and logging \"Hot Reload: Active\" upon file changes. After that, I will review `dmarket_api.py` and `trade_logic.py`, determining the necessary code additions for DMarket client upgrades and steam background thread implementation. Finally, I will address the documentation and the profit scan task, making sure that I am able to run tests without live API access.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158297594_673","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/dmarket_api.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158297713_674","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/trade_logic.py"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":24811,"output":623,"cacheRead":21770,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25434,"cost":{"input":0.049622,"output":0.007476,"cacheRead":0.004354,