{"type":"message","id":"94ff1a77","parentId":"0fdf4d38","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:25:37.354Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Integrating Asynchronous Updates**\n\nI'm currently working on incorporating the asynchronous Steam update into `dmarket/trade_logic.py`. The challenge is to make sure `monitor_prices` doesn't get blocked. I'll need to carefully manage the asynchronous calls to prevent performance bottlenecks.\n\n\n**Refactoring Trade Logic**\n\nI'm now refactoring `trade_logic.py`, aiming to introduce an asynchronous structure as requested. Specifically, I'm converting the synchronous `TradeManager` class and its `monitor_prices` method to an asynchronous implementation. This will allow for the concurrent execution of Steam price updates without blocking the main loop. I'll integrate `asyncio.create_task` to achieve the desired non-blocking behavior.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771158337350_681","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/src/dmarket/trade_logic.py","content":"\"\"\"Trade logic for DMarket bot.\n\nThis module handles the core trading logic, including monitoring prices\nand making buy/sell decisions based on configured thresholds.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nimport asyncio\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any\nimport dmarket_api\n\n# Configure logging\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format='%(asctime)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s')\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\nclass TradeManager:\n    \"\"\"Manages trading operations and price monitoring.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, api_client: Any) -> None:\n        self.api = api_client\n        self.steam_prices = {}\n        self.running = False\n\n    async def update_steam_prices(self):\n        \"\"\"Background task to update Steam prices every 10 minutes.\"\"\"\n        while self.running:\n            try:\n                logger.info(\"Updating Steam prices...\")\n                # Mock Steam API call or call actual Steam integration here\n                # In a real scenario, this would call a steam_api wrapper\n                # self.steam_prices = await steam_api.get_prices()\n                await asyncio.sleep(600)  # 10 minutes\n            except Exception as e:\n                logger.error(f\"Error updating Steam prices: {e}\")\n                await asyncio.sleep(60)\n\n    async def monitor_prices(self, game_id: str = \"a8db\", threshold_price: float = 5.0) -> None:\n        \"\"\"\n        Main monitoring loop.\n        MUST NOT await Steam calls directly.\n        \"\"\"\n        self.running = True\n        \n        # Start Steam background thread\n        asyncio.create_task(self.update_steam_prices())\n        \n        logger.info(f\"Starting price monitor for game {game_id}...\")\n        \n        while self.running:\n            try:\n                # DMarket API call (fast)\n                items: List[Dict[str, Any]] = self.api.get_market_prices(game_id)\n                \n                if items and not isinstance(items, dict): # Check if valid list\n                    for item in items:\n                        self._process_item(item, threshold_price)\n                \n                await asyncio.sleep(5) # Poll interval\n                \n            except Exception as e:\n                logger.error(f\"Error in monitor loop: {e}\")\n                await asyncio.sleep(5)\n\n    def _process_item(self, item: Dict[str, Any], threshold: float):\n        try:\n            price = float(item.get('price', {}).get('USD', 999999))\n            title = item.get('title', 'Unknown')\n            \n            # Simple logic using cached steam prices if available\n            steam_price = self.steam_prices.get(title)\n            \n            if price < threshold:\n                logger.info(f\"Potential Buy: {title} at {price} USD\")\n                \n        except Exception:\n            pass\n"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":28676,"output":920,"cacheRead":24958,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29596,"cost":{"input":0.057352,"output":0.01104,"cacheRead":0.0049916000000000006,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0733836}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771158325112}}
